race.comment: MANGIFERA (6) made it back-to-back wins last start by 0.2L when sitting up front at Bunbury in a CL3. She looks a mare on the way up and Fiore remains in the saddle. Needs some luck from the wide draw, but she's trending the right way and can continue her winning ways. SHOW THE WAY (7) wasn't beaten far last start when flying home from the back of the pack over 1400m here a fortnight ago. He's drawn out again so he's likely to get back in the run again, though the rise in trip should suit. Hasn't won for a while but he's back in good order and can go one better here. FOREVER DREAMING (4) has gone under in a photo her past couple and drops back to the 1500m journey today. Her form over the mile two back was solid and she maps for a cosy run in transit. Can get back to winning ways. JAZALOT (10) is not out of this with the rise in trip suiting. GINGER AND TONIC (9) is better than we saw last start and can bounce back.
